*  Primary engines (feedback_primary_engines_apr14.md) — "MAX" = MiniMax M2.7, NOT Opus. Gemini for deep analysis.
*  Continuous build (feedback_forges_never_stop.md) — Workers must stay in a continuous build loop. Idle = failure.
*  Kimi headless (feedback_kimi_yolo_required.md) — kimi -p without -y hangs on permission prompt. Required protocol.
*  tmux paste (feedback_tmux_paste_enter_gotcha.md) — send-keys traps Enter. Use -l + separate Enter; verify with capture.
*  Diagrams first (feedback_diagrams_first.md) — Always lead with ASCII diagram for bugs/fixes. Prose only if asked.
*  Artifacts visuals (feedback_artifacts_diagram_first.md) — All artifacts must lead with ASCII/visual diagram.
*  Opus debugging (feedback_opus_for_analysis.md) — Dispatch Opus subagents for complex debugging; Sonnet misses edges.
*  Opus writes (feedback_opus_for_file_writes.md) — Always dispatch Write/Edit to Opus subagents; Sonnet stays read-only.
*  Opus task select (feedback_opus_task_selection.md) — Task selection must go through Opus subagent, never Sonnet.
*  Computer use (feedback_computer_use.md) — Use Chrome control for Railway/X/Vercel checks instead of asking Alex.
*  Do the work (feedback_do_the_work.md) — Never pause to ask "want me to do X?" — just execute the obvious next step.
*  Codex batching (feedback_codex_batching.md) — Batch-run Codex from CC; store prompts in /tmp, not repo.
*  Style (feedback_response_style.md) — Concise, action-first, no summaries, parallel execution mindset.
*  Codex model (feedback_codex_model.md) — Always use gpt-5.4, never o4-mini.
*  Codex sandbox (feedback_codex_cli_sandbox.md) — Use --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox for worktree dispatch.
